  "decision_conditions": [
    "The Cedar and Horse Chestnut as situated within the front garden of St Raphaels Convent, with Court Drive frequently used as a cut through they are highly visible to many passers-by and residents, as a result they have high amenity values. They also significantly contribute to the arboricultural character of Hillingdon Court Park Area of Special Local Character (ASLC).",
    "The work proposed to the Horse Chestnut is seen as excessive and will lead to multiple large wounds throughout the trees canopy which could lead to dysfunction and decline, furthermore \"light penetration\" is not seen as a valid arboricultural reason for the work. The reasons behind the work for the Cedar are contradictory the applicant wishes to carry out the work to encourage lateral spread but they also with to increase light penetration, the Cedars form is currently seen as appropriate for its location.",
    "Having regard to the reasons given for the proposed work, the work is unjustified and will have a detrimental im",
    "The removal of deadwood, dangerous / hanging branches and ivy:  This does not require the formal consent of the Council."
